The paper discusses security and privacy concerns in location-based services, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a decentralized system, which involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and potentially requires efficient algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions pseudonymous authentication, which is a topic in cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the practicality of the proposed design, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
